description: Blend of Jill (“female given name, colloquial counterpart to Jack”) + jackaroo.

entries.meaning: (Australia) A female jackaroo, a woman who does the job of a jackaroo.
examples: She left school at thirteen-years-of-age to work with her father as a jillaroo: building fences, mustering cattle, and working at various jobs on stations throughout Queensland and New South Wales.
